From: User-3090 <71881005+User-3090@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 14:02:11 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 8/8] fix(windows): allow controlled app-local ConPTY

Replace the force-system portable-pty patch with an explicit app-local loader.
It derives an absolute conpty.dll path from current_exe, never probes PATH,
requires every OpenConsole host architecture needed by the executable, rejects
partial bundles, and retains kernel32.dll as the fallback when no bundle exists.

Update the vendored-patch record, make its Windows path check portable, and
extend the existing smoke helper so a caller can assert the expected app-local
OpenConsole process. Keep package discovery, floating-version selection, and
fork-only build, nightly, and release workflows out of this patch.

Extracted from the ConPTY portions of 006886c96c9f98f4056894d5da402b22188e79fc,
f3fac551ece1b3f05276bb60f33ed16fbd487f70, and
619414627c158a794c2a5714e74e4fd699211a60.

refs #761
refs #1528
